      "SummaryText": "RISK MANAGEMENT PLAN\r\n\r\n\r\nFOR:\tANHYDROUS AMMONIA HANDLING\r\n\r\n\t\t\r\nAT THE\r\nVERTELLUS HEALTH & SPECIALTY PRODUCTS LLC\r\nMANUFACTURING FACILITY\r\nDELAWARE WATER GAP, PA\r\n\r\nIN COMPLIANCE WITH 40 CFR 68\r\n\r\nJanuary 31, 2013\r\n(Replaces January 31, 2008)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nKevinn P. Kramer\r\nVERTELLUS HEALTH & SPECIALTY PRODUCTS LLC\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY\r\nThe facility policy is to adhere, at a minimum, to the applicable Federal and state rules and regulations that govern accidental release prevention and emergency response. The facility has policies and programs for accidental releases and spills and emergency response.\r\n\r\nThe facility conforms to and has been certified to the American Chemistry Council's (ACC) Responsible Care&reg; initiative.  Responsible Care&reg; enables chemical companies to achieve even higher standards of performance. The Responsible Care Management System offers an integrated, structured approach to improve company performance in the following key areas: community awareness and emergency response; security; distribution; employee health and safety; pollution prevention; and process and product safety. \r\n \r\nThe facility manufactures Ammonia salts and many other specialty chemical products.\r\n\r\nThe facility handles anhydrous ammonia to produce ammonia salts.\r\n\r\nTha Facility stores 51,840 lbs. of anhydrous ammonia.\r\n\r\nAmmonia is stored in tank that has a maximum volume of 12,000 gal. Our unloading procedure requires operators to fill to no greater than 80% of capacity or 9600 gallons.  Based on a density of 5.4 lb/gal at 20\u00b0F, that corresponds to a weight of 51,840 lb or 23,600 kg when converted to kilograms and rounded up to the nearest 100 kg.\r\n\r\nA strong emphasis is placed on worker safety and accident prevention.  Conscientious efforts by trained personnel ensure that the facility operates within the guidelines established by the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) and its Process Safety Management Program.  Training and experience pre"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000032777,
      "SummaryText": "pares them to manage operations on a 24-hour a day, 7-day a week schedule.   \r\n\r\nThe facility has not had any reportable accidents from covered processes in the past 5-years.  \r\n\r\nAn emergency response plan for the facility has been prepared and provided to emergency responders, including Monroe County LEPC (local emergency planning committee), local Fire companies, and the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Resources.  The facility was recognized in 1996 by the USEPA (United States Environmental Protection Agency) with the presentation of the Partnership Award.  The award recognizes extraordinary contributions to chemical emergency preparedness and prevention programs."
